<h2 id="how-we-produce-statistics">How we produce statistics</h2>

<p>Our statement of compliance gives details of our policies and strategies that ensure that we are compliant with the UK Statistics Authority Code of Practice for Statistics (2018). These include our policies on revisions, data management, statement of administrative sources, user engagement and complaints.</p>

<p><span id="attachment_3075407" class="attachment-inline">
  <a href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/427590/Compliance_Statement_-_May_2015.pdf">DCMS Statement of Compliance </a>
  (<span class="type"><abbr title="Portable Document Format">PDF</abbr></span>, <span class="file-size">742KB</span>, <span class="page-length">25 pages</span>)
</span></p>

<p><span id="attachment_3075408" class="attachment-inline">
  <a href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/430327/DCMS_Statement_of_Adminstrative_Sources_March_2015.xls">DCMS Statement of Administrative Sources</a>
  (<span class="type">MS Excel Spreadsheet</span>, <span class="file-size">65.5KB</span>)
</span></p>

<p>DCMS also publish annual <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/statistical-work-plans">statistical work plans</a>.</p>

<h2 id="uk-statistics-authority-assessment-of-the-dcms-sectors-economic-estimates-series">UK statistics authority assessment of the DCMS Sectors Economic Estimates series</h2>

<p>In 2017 the department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport (DCMS) asked the Office for Statistics Regulation to assess the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dcms-sectors-economic-estimates">DCMS Sectors Economic Estimates series</a> for designation as National Statistics. <a rel="external" href="https://www.statisticsauthority.gov.uk/about-the-authority/uk-statistical-system/types-of-official-statistics/">National Statistics</a> are those which have been found to meet all the criteria set out in the <a rel="external" href="https://www.statisticsauthority.gov.uk/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/Code-of-Practice-for-Statistics.pdf">Code of Practice for Statistics</a> and which can therefore be considered to be trustworthy, high quality, and of value to the public.</p>

<p>On 6 December 2018 the Office for Statistics Regulation recommended that the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dcms-sectors-economic-estimates">Economic Estimates series</a> be designated as National Statistics, subject to meeting the six requirements set out in the <a rel="external" href="https://www.statisticsauthority.gov.uk/correspondence/dcms-sectors-economic-estimates/">assessment report</a>.</p>

<p>To meet these requirements we will conduct a review of the DCMS sector definitions and methodology. The review will consult users and producers of DCMS sector economic statistics on how DCMS sectors are defined, the range of data sources available, and the appetite for more granular demographic information. We anticipate that consultation will begin in 2019. If you would like to be involved with the consultation or the review, please get in touch at EconomicEstimates@culture.gov.uk. Further information will be published in due course.</p>

<p>We will also include additional or expanded documentation as part of our standard publication cycle. Relevant documents include the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dcms-sectors-economic-estimates-methodology">DCMS Sectors Economic Estimates methodology guide</a>, the quality assurance guides for each publication, and the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/427590/Compliance_Statement_-_May_2015.pdf">DCMS Statement of Compliance</a>.</p>

<h2 id="other-uk-statistics-authority-assessments">Other UK statistics authority assessments</h2>

<p>In 2012 the UK Statistics Authority published its assessment of DCMS as a producer of Official Statistics. The Authority assessed DCMS against the Code of Practice for Official Statistics.</p>

<p>You can view the <a rel="external" href="https://www.google.co.uk/url?sa=t&rct=j&q=&esrc=s&source=web&cd=1&ved=0CC8QFjAA&url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.statisticsauthority.gov.uk%2Fassessment%2Fassessment%2Fassessment-reports%2Fassessment-report-190---statistics-on-participation-in-culture--leisure-and-sport.pdf&ei=ZLYtUfWoA-iI0AWWyoG4BA&usg=AFQjCNHhBqanbyJJXe9FOfjHK0VnFWQXaw&bvm=bv.42965579,d.d2k">assessment report on the UK Statistics Authority website</a> (PDF, 76kb). The main focus of the report is on the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/taking-part-survey">Taking Part survey</a>, but the Authority also comments more widely on DCMS as a producer of Official Statistics.</p>

<p>On 12 February 2013 the Board of the Statistics Authority designated Taking Part outputs as National Statistics in a letter to the department.</p>

<p>On 24 January 2018, at the request of DCMS, the Board of the Statistics Authority dedesignated Entertainment Licensing Statistics from National Statistics.</p>

<p><span id="attachment_3075406" class="attachment-inline">
  <a href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/105744/Letter_of_Confirmation_as_National_Statistics_-_Assessment_Report_190.pdf">Assessment of statistics on culture, leisure and sport</a>
  (<span class="type"><abbr title="Portable Document Format">PDF</abbr></span>, <span class="file-size">42.3KB</span>, <span class="page-length">2 pages</span>)
</span></p>

